{{Year dab|1280}}
{{Year nav|1280}}
{{C13 year in topic}}'''1280''' ('''[[Roman numerals|MCCLXXX]]''') was a [[leap year starting on Monday]] (link will display the full calendar) in the [[Julian calendar]].

== Events ==
&lt;onlyinclude&gt;
* [[June 23]] &amp;ndash; [[Reconquista]] &amp;ndash; [[Battle of Moclín (1280)|Battle of Moclín]]: Troops of the [[Emirate of Granada]] defeat those of the [[Kingdom of Castile]], and [[Kingdom of León]].&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=6HqbCwAAQBAJ&amp;pg=PA121&amp;dq=1280+Battle+of+Mocl%C3%ADn#q=1280%20Battle%20of%20Mocl%C3%ADn|title=The Mercenary Mediterranean: Sovereignty, Religion, and Violence in the Medieval Crown of Aragon|last=Fancy|first=Hussein|publisher=University of Chicago Press|year=2016|isbn=9780226329789|location=Chicago and London|pages=121|language=en}}&lt;/ref&gt;
* Construction on the northern section of the [[Grand Canal of China]] is begun.&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=l6TVhvYLaEwC&amp;pg=PA359&amp;dq=1280+Grand+Canal+China#q=1280%20Grand%20Canal%20China|title=Science and Civilisation in China: Volume 4, Physics and Physical Technology, Part 3, Civil Engineering and Nautics|last1=Needham|first1=Joseph|last2=Ling|first2=Wang|last3=Gwei-Djen|first3=Lu|publisher=Cambridge University Press|year=2000|isbn=9780521070607|volume=IV|location=Cambridge, New York, Melbourne, Madrid|pages=359|language=en|orig-year=1971}}&lt;/ref&gt;
* The final expansion of [[Lincoln Cathedral]] in [[Kingdom of England|England]] is completed.&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite book|chapter-url=https://books.google.com/books?id=uzQrDwAAQBAJ&amp;pg=PA158&amp;dq=1280+lincoln+cathedral#q=1280%20lincoln%20cathedral|title=Bishop Robert Grosseteste and Lincoln Cathedral: Tracing Relationships between Medieval Concepts of Order and Built Form|last=Frost|first=Christian|publisher=Routledge|year=2016|isbn=9781351573580|editor-last=Temple|editor-first=Nicholas|location=Abingdon and New York|pages=158|language=en|chapter=Architecture, Liturgy and Processions: Bishop Grosseteste's Lincoln and Bishop Poore's Salisbury|orig-year=2014|editor-last2=Hendrix|editor-first2=John Shannon|editor-last3=Frost|editor-first3=Christian}}&lt;/ref&gt;
* King [[Magnus III of Sweden]] founds a [[Swedish nobility]], by enacting a law accepting a contribution of a [[cavalry]]-member in lieu of ordinary tax payments.&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=EqtPAAAAMAAJ&amp;q=1280+swedish+nobility&amp;dq=1280+swedish+nobility|title=Roos Af Hjelmsäter: A Swedish Noble Family with Allied Families and Emigrants|last1=Crawford|first1=Lillie Rollins|last2=Crawford|first2=Robert Junious|publisher=Gateway Press|year=1996|isbn=|location=Baltimore, MD|pages=493|language=en}}&lt;/ref&gt;
* [[Tsar]] [[Ivan Asen III of Bulgaria]] flees from [[Tarnovo]], ending the [[Asen dynasty|Asen Dynasty]] in [[Bulgaria]].&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=LqxfDwAAQBAJ&amp;pg=PA966&amp;dq=1280+Ivan+Asen+III#q=1280%20Ivan%20Asen%20III|title=The Oxford Handbook of Byzantine Studies|last1=Jeffreys|first1=Elizabeth|last2=Haldon|first2=John|last3=Cormack|first3=Robin|publisher=Oxford University Press|year=2008|isbn=|location=Oxford, New York|pages=966|language=en}}&lt;/ref&gt;
* [[Syria]] attempts to secede from the [[Mamluk Sultanate (Cairo)|Mamluk Sultanate]] of [[Egypt]], but [[Al Mansur Qalawun]] defeats the rebels, and keeps Syria within the Egyptian sultanate.&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=WjQfo3a1eVMC&amp;pg=PA559&amp;dq=1280++syria+mamluk#q=1280%20%20syria%20mamluk|title=Conflict and Conquest in the Islamic World: A Historical Encyclopedia|last=Mikaberidze|first=Alexander|date=2011-07-31|publisher=ABC-CLIO |isbn=9781598843361|location=Santa Barbara, CA, Denver, CO and Oxford|pages=559|language=en}}&lt;/ref&gt;
* The second of two main surveys of the [[Hundred Rolls]], an English [[census]] seen as a follow up to the [[Domesday Book]] completed in [[1086]], is completed; it began in [[1279]].
* [[Turin]] is conquered by [[Thomas III of Savoy]], becoming the capital of the [[House of Savoy]].&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ndh9zotj5DcC&amp;pg=PA91&amp;dq=1280+Hundred+Rolls#q=1280%20Hundred%20Rolls|title=Lordship, Knighthood and Locality: A Study in English Society, C.1180-1280|last=Coss|first=Peter R.|publisher=Cambridge University Press|year=1991|isbn=9780521402965|location=Cambridge, New York, Melbourne|pages=91|language=en}}&lt;/ref&gt;
* Approximate date
** The Ancestors of the [[Māori people]] from eastern [[Polynesia]] become the first human settlers of [[New Zealand]].&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=abNDLZQ6quYC&amp;pg=PA172&amp;dq=1280+Maori+new+zealand#q=1280%20Maori%20new%20zealand|title=Ethnic Groups of South Asia and the Pacific: An Encyclopedia|last=Minahan|first=James|publisher=ABC-CLIO|year=2012|isbn=9781598846591|location=Santa Barbara, CA, Denver, CO and Oxford|pages=172|language=en}}&lt;/ref&gt;
** The Wolf minimum of [[solar variation|solar activity]] begins.&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite book|chapter-url=https://books.google.com/books?id=6Ya6BQAAQBAJ&amp;pg=PA15&amp;dq=1280+wolf+minimum+solar#q=1280%20wolf%20minimum%20solar|title=Solar and Heliospheric Origins of Space Weather Phenomena|last1=Rozelot|first1=Jean-Pierre|last2=Lefebvre|first2=Sandrine|publisher=Springer|year=2006|isbn=9783540337591|editor-last=Rozelot|editor-first=Jean-Pierre|series=Lecture Notes in Physics|volume=699|location=Berlin, Heidelberg, New York|pages=15|language=en|chapter=Advances in Understanding Elements of the Sun - Earth Links}}&lt;/ref&gt;

== Births ==
* [[Birger, King of Sweden]], Swedish monarch (d. [[1321]])&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=yqu8CgAAQBAJ&amp;pg=PA31&amp;dq=1280+-+1321++Birger,+King+of+Sweden#q=1280%20-%201321%20%20Birger,%20King%20of%20Sweden|title=The Revelations of St Birgitta: A Study and Edition of the Birgittine-Norwegian Texts, Swedish National Archives, E 8902|last=Adams|first=Jonathan|publisher=BRILL|year=2016|isbn=9789004304666|location=Leiden. Boston|pages=31|language=en}}&lt;/ref&gt;
* [[Wu Zhen (painter)|Wu Zhen]], Chinese painter (d. [[1354]])&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=TlVeuxIgjwQC&amp;pg=PA75&amp;dq=1280+wu+zhen#q=1280%20wu%20zhen|title=Gardner's Art through the Ages: Non-Western Perspectives|last=Kleiner|first=Fred S.|publisher=Cengage Learning|year=2010|isbn=9780495573678|location=Boston, MA|pages=75|language=en}}&lt;/ref&gt;
* ''Approximate date''
** [[Anna of Kashin]], Russian saint (d. [[1368]])&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite web|url=https://www.stkatherineorthodoxchurch.org/stannaofkashin.html|title=St. Anna of Kashin|website=www.stkatherineorthodoxchurch.org|access-date=2019-03-06}}&lt;/ref&gt;
** [[Musa I of Mali]], West African emperor (d. c.[[1337]])

== Deaths ==
* [[February 10]] &amp;ndash; [[Margaret II, Countess of Flanders]] (b. [[1202]])&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=QrmV4AHFnrgC&amp;pg=PA142&amp;dq=1280+Margaret+II,+Countess+of+Flanders#q=1280%20Margaret%20II,%20Countess%20of%20Flanders|title=Women Leaders of Europe and the Western Hemisphere: A Biographical Reference|last=Jackson|first=Guida M.|publisher=Xlibris Corporation|year=2009|isbn=9781469113548|location=Bloomington, IN|pages=142–143|language=en}}&lt;/ref&gt;
* [[May 9]] &amp;ndash; [[Magnus VI of Norway]]&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=WTUXAAAAYAAJ&amp;pg=PA45&amp;dq=1280+Magnus+VI#q=1280%20Magnus%20VI|title=Visit to Northern Europe: Or, Sketches Descriptive, Historical, Political and Moral, of Denmark, Norway, Sweden and Finland, and the Free Cities of Hamburg and Lubeck, Containing Notices of the Manners and Customs, Commerce , Manufactures, Arts and Sciences , Education, Literature and Religion, of Those Countries and Cities|last=Baird|first=Robert|publisher=J.S. Taylor &amp; Company|year=1842|isbn=|volume=II|location=New York|pages=45|language=en}}&lt;/ref&gt;
* [[August 22]] &amp;ndash; [[Pope Nicholas III]] (b. [[1218]])&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=BhyOAQAAQBAJ&amp;pg=PA479&amp;dq=1280+Pope+Nicholas+III#q=1280%20Pope%20Nicholas%20III|title=Key Figures in Medieval Europe: An Encyclopedia|last1=Emmerson|first1=Richard K.|last2=Clayton-Emmerson|first2=Sandra|publisher=Routledge|year=2006|isbn=9781136775192|location=New York, London|pages=479|language=en}}&lt;/ref&gt;
* [[November 15]] &amp;ndash; [[Albertus Magnus]], German theologian&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=dL1ac3yFjF8C&amp;pg=PA9&amp;dq=1280+Albert+Magnus#q=1280%20Albert%20Magnus|title=A Companion to Albert the Great: Theology, Philosophy, and the Sciences|last=Resnick|first=Irven|publisher=BRILL|year=2013|isbn=9789004234079|series=Brill's Companions to the Christian Tradition|location=Leiden, Boston|pages=9|language=en}}&lt;/ref&gt;
