{{Year dab|
1281}}
{{refimprove|date=August 2017}}
{{Year nav|1281}}
{{C13 year in topic}}Year '''1281''' ('''[[Roman numerals|MCCLXXXI]]''') was a [[common year starting on Wednesday]] (link will display the full calendar) of the [[Julian calendar]].

== Events ==
&lt;onlyinclude&gt;
=== By place ===
==== Asia ====
* [[August 15]] &amp;ndash; [[Battle of Kōan]] (Hakata Bay): The second [[Mongol Empire|Mongol]] [[Mongol invasions of Japan|invasion of Japan]] is foiled, as a large [[typhoon]] &amp;ndash; famously called a ''[[Kamikaze (typhoon)|kamikaze]]'', or divine wind &amp;ndash; destroys much of the combined Chinese and Korean fleet and forces, numbering over 140,000 men and 4,000 ships.
* [[Kublai Khan]] orders the burning of sacred [[Taoism|Taoist]] texts, resulting in the reduction in number of volumes of the ''[[Daozang]]'' (Taoist Canon) from 4,565 to 1,120.
* The [[Mon (ethnic group)|Mon]] Kingdom of [[Hariphunchai]] falls, as its capital [[Lamphun]] (in present-day [[Thailand]]) is captured by King [[Mangrai]]'s [[Lanna]]thai Kingdom.

===== Middle East =====
* [[October 29]] &amp;ndash; [[Second Battle of Homs]]: [[Mamluk Sultanate (Cairo)|Mamluk]] sultan [[Qalawun]] defeats an invasion of [[Syria]], by [[Mongol Empire|Mongol]] [[Ilkhanate|Ilkhan]] [[Abaqa Khan]]. 
* [[Osman I]], founder of the [[Ottoman Empire]], becomes ''[[bey]]'' of the [[Söğüt]] tribe in central [[Anatolia]]; in [[1299]] he will declare independence from the [[Seljuk Turks]], marking the birth of the Ottoman Empire.
* An offensive by the [[Byzantine Empire]] significantly reduces the size of the [[Kingdom of Albania (medieval)|Kingdom of Albania]], as it recaptures land seized from the [[Despotate of Epirus]] by [[Charles I of Sicily]] 10 years earlier.

==== Europe ====
* [[Pope Martin IV]] authorizes a [[Crusade]] against the newly re-established [[Byzantine Empire]] in [[Constantinople]]; French and [[Venice|Venetian]] expeditions set out toward Constantinople, but are forced to turn back in the following year.
* July &amp;ndash; Niccolò Bonsignori heads a hundred of [[Ghibelline]] exiles, in a failed attempt to topple the [[Republic of Siena|Sienese]] government.

===By topic===
====Markets====
* [[Guy of Dampierre]], count of [[County of Flanders|Flanders]], licenses the first Lombard merchants to open a changing business in his realm.&lt;ref&gt;{{cite journal|last=Munro|first=John H.|title=The Medieval Origins of the Financial Revolution|journal=The International History Review|year=2003|volume=15|issue=3|pages=506–562}}&lt;/ref&gt;

====Religion====
* [[Pope Martin IV]] succeeds [[Pope Nicholas III]], as the 189th [[pope]].
&lt;/onlyinclude&gt;

== Births ==
* [[December 25]] &amp;ndash; [[Alice de Lacy, 4th Countess of Lincoln]] (d. [[1348]])
* [[Castruccio Castracani]], duke of [[Lucca]] (d. [[1328]])
* [[Yuri III Danilovich]], Grand Prince of Russia (d. [[1325]])
* [[Agnes of Austria (1281–1364)|Agnes of Austria]], queen consort of Hungary (d. [[1364]])
* [[Henry, 3rd Earl of Lancaster]] (d. [[1345]])
* [[Hamdallah Mustawfi]], Ilkhanid Iranian historian (d. [[1349]])
* [[Rudolf I of Bohemia]] (d. [[1307]])
* [[Sancia of Majorca]], queen consort and regent of Naples (approximate date) (d. [[1345]])

== Deaths ==
* [[February 16]] &amp;ndash; [[Gertrude of Hohenberg]], queen consort of Germany (b. c.1225)
* [[September 10]] &amp;ndash; [[John II, Margrave of Brandenburg-Stendal]] (b. [[1237]])
* [[October 8]] &amp;ndash; Princess [[Constance of Greater Poland]] (b. c.1245)
* [[December 24]] &amp;ndash; [[Henry V, Count of Luxembourg]] (b. [[1216]])
* ''date unknown'' &amp;ndash; [[Ertuğrul]], Turkish father of [[Osman I]] (b. [[1198]])

